      "content": "a hobby? a walk? how is that supposed to help when the half of me that made life worth living is gone? it's like trying to patch a hole in a ship that's already at the bottom of the ocean. i look at the empty side of the bed and it's just... it's too much to carry. i'm exhausted from just existing in this emptiness. it feels like there's no version of the future where i'm not just a shadow of who i was.",
